          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a Hindu philosophical treatise written from the perspective of the Advaita Vedānta school of philosophy. The work is a super-commentary (vārttika) on the Pañcīkaraṇa by Śaṅkarācārya. Work describes the stages of cosmic evolution, the role of the mantra Oṃ, as well as the place of the Self and its realization within that process of evolution.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Pañcīkaraṇavārttika</title>
              <title type="vernacular">पञ्चीकरणवार्त्तिक</title>
              <author>
                <persName type="authority">Sureśvarācārya</persName>
              </author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīparamahaṃsaparivrājakācāryapūjyapādaśiṣyaśrīsuraścarācāryaviracitapaṃcīkaraṇavārtikaṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // (f. 8v).</colophon>
